4. Relationships & Marriage

Love vs. arranged: Mixed-favorable for love marriage or a self-chosen relationship. Your lagna lord and Atmakaraka (the planet representing your soul's strongest desire), Venus, sits in your 11th house of friendships and social circles — a classic signature for meeting a partner through your own network rather than strictly through formal introduction. That said, with Saturn's heavy influence in this chart, even a "love" connection is likely to mature in a fairly grounded, slow-building, eventually-formalized way rather than anything impulsive.

Mangal Dosha: Present technically (Mars in 7th house) but cancelled because Mars sits in its own sign (Aries). If this comes up in traditional matchmaking conversations, it's worth mentioning the cancellation explicitly — most classically trained astrologers will recognize it.

Navamsa (D9) check: In your D9 chart, Venus (your 7th-house-of-marriage significator and Atmakaraka) sits in Libra — its own sign. This is a strong, favorable signal for marital harmony: it suggests a spouse who is genuinely compatible in temperament, likely charming, balanced, and relationship-oriented rather than someone who creates chronic friction.

Spouse characteristics (Mars in Aries, 7th house, own sign): Likely someone energetic, direct, possibly career-driven or athletic in temperament, with a strong independent streak — not a passive personality.

